      "rationale": "Newton-Raphson iterations converged to force residuals below 1e-7 for all 47 load steps across all model configurations. Energy balance checks confirmed no artificial energy dissipation. Solver settings documented in the analysis report."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent review of model setup, boundary conditions, and material assignments performed by a second analyst not involved in model construction.",
      "rationale": "An independent senior analyst reviewed all boundary condition definitions, material property assignments, contact pair definitions, and loading protocols against the ASTM F1717 standard requirements. No discrepancies were identified. Review documented in the project record."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Constitutive model (bilinear isotropic hardening) validated against Ti-6Al-4V coupon data; geometric fidelity confirmed against CAD drawings.",
      "rationale": "Bilinear isotropic hardening plasticity (E=114 GPa, yield=880 MPa, tangent=1.2 GPa) was calibrated against Ti-6Al-4V dog-bone tensile coupon data from the same material lot. Geometric fidelity of the FEA model was confirmed against certified CAD drawings with maximum deviation of 0.05 mm."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties sourced from certified material test reports for the same material lot as test specimens; dimensional inputs from CMM measurements.",
      "rationale": "Elastic modulus, yield strength, and ultimate tensile strength were taken from certified material test reports for the Ti-6Al-4V bar stock used to manufacture the test specimens. Critical dimensions (screw outer diameter, rod diameter, pedicle block geometry) were verified by coordinate measuring machine reports."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N≥10 constructs tested; specimens from production-equivalent manufacturing; dimensional inspection completed.",
      "rationale": "Eleven non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs were tested across two independent laboratories. All specimens were manufactured from the same material lot and production-equivalent process. Dimensional inspection confirmed conformance to drawing tolerances for all 11 specimens."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions replicate intended COU loading environment; multiple load configurations evaluated.",
      "rationale": "Testing was conducted strictly per ASTM F1717 at a single compression-bending load configuration (5° offset). While this matches the regulatory standard, only one load condition was evaluated, limiting confidence in model generalizability across the full loading envelope. This factor is below the required level and is a documented limitation of the study."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA boundary conditions demonstrably equivalent to experimental fixture constraints; loading protocol matches test machine displacement control.",
      "rationale": "The ASTM F1717 pedicle block fixture geometry was explicitly modeled in the FEA as rigid bodies with frictional contact (μ=0.3). Displacement-controlled loading at 5 mm/min was replicated as quasi-static displacement increments. Equivalency confirmed by comparing reaction force profiles between FEA and test machine load cell records."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric E/uval < 1.96 for all QoIs; percent difference < 10%.",
      "rationale": "All three QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) satisfied both acceptance criteria. E/uval values of 0.81, 1.14, and 1.72 are all below 1.96. Percent differences of 4.7%, 6.2%, and 8.9% are all below 10%. The model is considered validated for the stated COU."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs directly linked to device failure modes and regulatory submission requirements.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are the three QoIs specified in ASTM F1717 and required by FDA guidance for pedicle screw 510(k) submissions. These QoIs directly characterize the structural failure modes of clinical relevance (permanent deformation and fracture)."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
